## P0-B: Actian VectorAI Explorer Page ⭐ (THE KILLER FEATURE)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is what will WIN the hackathon. Judges need to SEE Actian being used deeply. A dedicated page showing all 14 collections with live search capability is the ultimate proof.

### [NEW] `src/pages/VectorExplorer.jsx` + `VectorExplorer.css`

**What it shows:**
1. **Collection Grid** — 14 glassmorphism cards, one per Actian collection, showing doc count and last-updated timestamp
2. **Live Semantic Search** — A search bar where judges type a query (e.g., "fraud in textile company") and see real-time results from Actian VectorAI with similarity scores
3. **Hybrid Search Demo** — A toggle for metadata filters (application_id, agent, phase) alongside vector search
4. **Collection Inspector** — Click any collection card → see recent documents, embeddings (truncated), metadata
5. **Pipeline Attribution** — Each document shows which agent wrote it and when

**UI Design:**
- Dark theme matching existing glassmorphism `glass-strong` styling
- Animated similarity score bars (framer-motion)
- Real-time search with debounce (300ms)
- Recharts horizontal bar chart for similarity scores

**Layout:**
