## P0-C: Live Agent Pipeline Visualizer

### [NEW] `src/pages/AgentPipeline.jsx` + `AgentPipeline.css`

**What it shows:**
A Sankey-style or node-graph view of all 14 agents with real-time status. As agents process, their nodes light up green with pulse animations. Lines between agents show data flow.

**Layout:**
```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  🔄 Agent Pipeline — Application #abc-1234                  │
├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                            │
│  [Compliance] ──✅──▶ [Doc Agent] ──✅──▶ [GST Agent]      │
│       │                    │                    │          │
│       │              [Bank Recon] ──✅     [MCA Agent]     │
│       │                    │                    │          │
│       ▼                    ▼                    ▼          │
│  [Web Agent] ──⏳──▶ [Model Sel.] ──▶ [Risk Agent]        │
│       │                                   │               │
│       ▼                                   ▼               │
│  [PD Agent]           [Bias] ←── [Stress Agent]           │
│       │                 │                                  │
│       ▼                 ▼                                  │
│              [CAM Generator] ──✅──▶ 📄 Final Report       │
│                                                            │
│  [Monitor Agent 👁️ — watching all events]                   │
│  [PAN Agent 🆔 — running in parallel]                      │
│                                                            │
│  ── Actian VectorAI Traffic ──                             │
│  ⬆️ 47 upserts  ⬇️ 23 searches  📊 14 collections         │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**How it works:**
- Subscribes to same WebSocket feed as existing `AgentFeedWidget`
- Each agent node tracks its status: `IDLE → PROCESSING → COMPLETED`
- Framer-motion pulse animation on active agents
- Counter at bottom shows Actian VectorAI operations in real-time
- Edge lines animate with a flowing gradient when data passes between agents

